      "problem": "Find the number of solutions to the congruence equation 55x ≡ 7 (mod 365).",
      "answer": "0",
      "source_code": "import random\n\nCONCEPT_TYPE = \"number_theory.crt_count\"\nCONCEPT_GROUP = \"number_theory\"\n\ndef generate(seed):\n    rng = random.Random(seed)\n\n    # Generate two co-prime integers a and b\n    a = rng.randint(2, 100)\n    b = rng.randint(2, 100)\n    while math.gcd(a, b) != 1:\n        a = rng.randint(2, 100)\n        b = rng.randint(2, 100)\n\n    # Generate a random modulus n\n    n = rng.randint(100, 1000)\n\n    # Compute the number of solutions to the congruence ax ≡ b (mod n)\n    solutions = 0\n\n    # Check for each x in the range [0, n-1]\n    for x in range(n):\n        if (a * x) % n == b:\n            solutions += 1\n\n    answer = solutions\n    problem = (\n        f\"Find the number of solutions to the congruence equation \"\n        f\"{a}x ≡ {b} (mod {n}).\"\n    )\n\n    return problem, str(answer)"
    },
