      "problem": "Consider a triangle with vertices at (2, 3), (-9, -2), and (6, 5). What is the area of the triangle? (Choose a technique: Shoelace formula or Heron's formula)",
      "answer": "1.0",
      "source_code": "import random\n\nCONCEPT_TYPE = \"geometry.trig_area\"\nCONCEPT_GROUP = \"geometry\"\n\ndef generate(seed):\n    rng = random.Random(seed)\n\n    # Generate random points for the triangle\n    x1, y1 = rng.randint(-10, 10), rng.randint(-10, 10)\n    x2, y2 = rng.randint(-10, 10), rng.randint(-10, 10)\n    x3, y3 = rng.randint(-10, 10), rng.randint(-10, 10)\n\n    # Calculate the area of the triangle using the shoelace formula\n    # Area = |(x1(y2 - y3) + x2(y3 - y1) + x3(y1 - y2)) / 2|\n    area = abs((x1 * (y2 - y3) + x2 * (y3 - y1) + x3 * (y1 - y2)) / 2)\n\n    # Introduce ambiguity by allowing multiple plausible techniques\n    # to solve the problem, such as using the shoelace formula or\n    # Heron's formula.\n    problem = (\n        f\"Consider a triangle with vertices at ({x1}, {y1}), ({x2}, {y2}), and ({x3}, {y3}). \"\n        f\"What is the area of the triangle? (Choose a technique: Shoelace formula or Heron's formula)\"\n    )\n\n    return problem, str(area)"
